               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus fragments of an astronomical calendar, recording the movements of heavenly bodies with reference to the signs of the Zodiac.</summary>
                  <msItem>
                     <note type="general">Margins: left (Fr. 1), 2 cm.; bottom (Fr. 1), 3.6 cm.; (Fr. 2), 3.8 cm.; on verso, in black ink: T 62.</note>
                     <note type="general">The columns are marked off by vertical black lines, while single horizontal lines, in red ink, have been inserted after each pair of months, and double horizontal lines, in red ink, above and below each group forming a year.</note>
                     <note type="general">The papyrus was found in a house within the temple area.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>5 papyri ; Frag. 1: 15.7 x 8.4 cm.; Frag. 2: 6.5 x 4 cm.; Frag. 3: 5 x 2.7 cm. and 2 smaller Frag.s</support>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <ab type="lines">13 cols. (56 lines) on recto along the fibers.</ab>
                           <ab type="recto-verso">Verso empty.</ab>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
